{{zh-forms|[[牡丹]][[花]][[下]][[死]]，[[做鬼]][[也]][[风流]]|[[牡丹花下死，做鬼也風流]]}}
==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: mŭdān huā xià sĭ, zuòguĭ yĕ fēngliú.
===Etymology===
Literally: If I should die beneath a [[Peony]] flower, I will still be amorous as a ghost.
*Note: [[Peony]] flower is a metaphor for a beautiful woman.

===Proverb===
# If I die under a skirt, I can still flirt as a ghost.<ref>From the English subtitles in the movie</ref>
# If my body should perish, girls I'll still cherish.<ref>From the dubbed English track in the movie</ref>

===Notes===
*source of both footnotes 1 and 2: ''[[w:House of Flying Daggers|House of Flying Daggers]]'' (Title 01 Chapter 06, about 10 seconds before Chapter 07), said by [[w:Takeshi Kaneshiro|Takeshi Kaneshiro]]'s character.  In the movie, he actually says: [[宁]][[在]][[花]][[下]][[死]]，[[做鬼]][[也]][[风流]] (Literally: "I would rather die under a flower; I will still be amorous, even as a ghost").
